===Verb===
{{en-verb|writes|writing|'''[[wrote]]''' ''or {{qualifier|archaic}}'' '''[[writ]]'''|'''[[written]]''' ''or {{qualifier|archaic}}'' '''[[writ]]'''}}

# {{ambitransitive}} To form letters, words or symbols on a surface in order to communicate.
#: ''The pupil '''wrote''' his name on the paper.''
#: ''Your son has been '''writing''' on the wall.''
# {{transitive}} To be the author of (a book, article, poem, etc.).
#: ''My uncle '''writes''' newspaper articles for The Herald.''
# {{transitive}} To send written information to.
#: ''Please '''write''' me when you get there.''
# {{transitive}} To show (information, etc) in written form.
#: ''The due day of the homework is '''written''' in the syllabus.''
# {{intransitive}} To be an author.
#: ''I '''write''' for a living.''
# {{context|transitive|computing}} To record (data) mechanically or electronically.
#: ''The computer writes to the disk faster than it reads from it.''
# {{South Africa|Canada|of a form, a document, etc.}} To [[fill in]], to [[complete]] using words.

